    <briefdescription>
<para>Value → position calibration for one gauge. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The DCS-BIOS value (0..65535) maps to a motor position. For a linear gauge, 0 → <computeroutput>minTravel</computeroutput> and 65535 → <computeroutput>maxTravel</computeroutput> (either may exceed the other or be negative — a centre-zero gauge sits mid-range). For a non-linear dial (airspeed, VVI), supply a piecewise curve: <computeroutput>curveIn</computeroutput> holds ascending DCS breakpoints and <computeroutput>curveOut</computeroutput> the matching positions (<computeroutput>curveN</computeroutput> entries); intermediate values are linearly interpolated.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para><computeroutput>curveOut</computeroutput> is unsigned — non-linear dials use a positive position range. Centre-zero gauges use the linear path (signed <computeroutput>minTravel</computeroutput> / <computeroutput>maxTravel</computeroutput>) instead. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
